      <h2>Capital Allowance: The Tax Benefit</h2>

      <p>When you buy equipment, you claim capital allowance:</p>

      <p><strong>Initial Allowance (Year 1):</strong>
      <br>• 20% to 40% of equipment cost
      <br>• Reduces taxable income immediately
      <br>• Biggest deduction in first year</p>

      <p><strong>Annual Allowance (Year 2+):</strong>
      <br>• 10% to 20% of remaining value
      <br>• Claimed every year until fully deducted
      <br>• Ongoing tax benefit</p>

      <p><strong>Example: RM100,000 Excavator</strong>
      <br>• Year 1 (40% initial): RM40,000 deduction
      <br>• Year 2 (20%): RM12,000 deduction
      <br>• Year 3 (20%): RM9,600 deduction
      <br>• Year 4 (20%): RM7,680 deduction
      <br>• Year 5 (20%): RM6,144 deduction
      <br><strong>Total Deductions:</strong> RM75,422</p>

      <h2>Timing Strategy: When to Buy</h2>

      <h3>Strategy 1: Buy Early in Tax Year</h3>

      <p>Buy in January/February:
      <br>• Full 12 months of deductions in Year 1
      <br>• Maximum tax benefit
      <br>• Cash flow preserved throughout year</p>

      <h3>Strategy 2: Buy Before Year-End</h3>

      <p>Buy in November/December:
      <br>• Still get full Year 1 initial allowance
      <br>• Purchase counts for current tax year
      <br>• Last-minute tax planning</p>

      <h3>Strategy 3: Spread Purchases</h3>

      <p>Buy equipment throughout the year:
      <br>• Consistent deductions each year
      <br>• Smooth tax planning
      <br>• Better cash flow management</p>

