      <p><strong>Preserve Cash Flow:</strong>
      <br>• No upfront payment
      <br>• Cash available for operations
      <br>• Can invest in business growth</p>

      <p><strong>Full Loan Amount:</strong>
      <br>• 100% of equipment cost financed
      <br>• More interest to deduct
      <br>• Larger tax benefit</p>

      <p><strong>Example: RM150,000 Excavator</strong>
      <br>• Bank (10% down): RM15,000 upfront + RM135,000 loan
      <br>• Ing Heng (0% down): RM0 upfront + RM150,000 loan
      <br><strong>Interest Savings:</strong> More loan = more interest deduction
      <br><strong>Cash Preserved:</strong> RM15,000 available for business</p>

      <h2>Used Equipment: More Tax Benefits</h2>

      <p>Used equipment offers unique advantages:</p>

      <p><strong>Lower Purchase Price:</strong>
      <br>• Used excavator: From RM34,000
      <br>• Used CAT: From RM50,000
      <br>• Used forklift: From RM15,000</p>

      <p><strong>Same Capital Allowance:</strong>
      <br>• Claim initial allowance on used equipment too
      <br>• Percentage applies to purchase price
      <br>• Faster full deduction due to lower cost</p>

      <p><strong>Banks Reject Used Equipment:</strong>
      <br>• Banks: 5-year age limit only
      <br>• Ing Heng: NO age limit
      <br>• Finance equipment up to 10+ years old</p>

      <h2>2026 Tax Deadlines</h2>

      <p>Key dates for 2026 tax planning:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>January 31:</strong> Final deadline for 2025 tax filing (for most businesses)</li>
        <li><strong>April 30:</strong> First quarterly tax installment (if applicable)</li>
